HEADWORD: Diatomous
<hw>Di*at"o*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>dia`tomos</grk> cut through, fr. <grk>diate`mnein</grk> to cut
through; <grk>dia`</grk> through + <grk>te`mnein</grk> to cut. Cf.
<er>Diatom</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Having a single,
distinct, diagonal cleavage; -- said of crystals.</def>
<rj><au>Mohs.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

